===Herbrand&#x27;s theorem===
Herbrand&#x27;s theorem states that the ramification groups in the lower numbering satisfy formula_115 (for formula_116 where formula_117 is the subextension corresponding to formula_60), and that the ramification groups in the upper numbering satisfy formula_119. This allows one to define ramification groups in the upper numbering for infinite Galois extensions (such as the absolute Galois group of a local field) from the inverse system of ramification groups for finite subextensions.

The upper numbering for an abelian extension is important because of the Hasse–Arf theorem. It states that if formula_1 is abelian, then the jumps in the filtration formula_108 are integers; i.e., formula_122 whenever formula_123 is not an integer.

The upper numbering is compatible with the filtration of the norm residue group by the unit groups under the Artin isomorphism. The image of formula_124 under the isomorphism

:formula_125

is just

